<br>
The Bandage Trick<br>
Dropping is a pain since EQ does not have a key map for dropping the item held on the cursor.  To drop an item, you must click on the play area.  Clicking the play area in a raid situation often unintentionally initiates a trade dialog.  Here's a way around it:<br>
<br>
You're likely already familiar with the &quot;auto equip&quot; window on the inventory screen.  Dropping an item here will send it to the best slot for that piece of equipment.  Dropping a rod on the auto equip window will send it to your primary hand or to an available inventory slot.  In the event no slot is available, the rod will instantly drop to the ground!<br>
<br>
To guarantee that a rod will fall to the ground, fill each open slot you have (primary inventory and bag slots) with a summoned bandage.   Voila!  You can now move among the raid party dropping rods like mad and never get a trade dialog or have to click a confirm box.<br>
<br>
In fact, since you likely have the rod spell on a hot key, you can leave the cursor over the auto equip and simply hotkey-click-hotkey-click...<br>
<br>
Note: Any stack of items can be used to do this.  I like to use bandages because they aren't edible.  If food or water are used for this trick, make sure that you have a stack of 10+ in the highest order inventory position. Otherwise, the next time you eat or drink, a slot will be empty and the rod will go to that slot.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
<br>
Moonwynd <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193326">Moon's Magelo Profile</A> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalamos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 8:08:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=353.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easily done</span><hr size=1> I always do the full inventory trick.  It's by far the best way to currently drop mod rods.  But still it's a minor annoyance having to spread bandages across all your open slots.  I agree that a /drop command should be added.<br>
