<br>
I do it pre-raid during the boring waiting around for people to show up, the same time I handle Focus item requests (and if you don;t get in early and ask me for them in response to my 17 announcements you better have a damn good reason!).<br>
<br>
Sure, I would like a /drop command, or even just another entry on the dropping preference selector thingummy (Never, Confirm, Always). Its just not a critical issue for me - compared to having to do the bloody job at all (making millions of rods) the task of filling up inventory slots is trivial. <br>
<br>
Consider it in terms of algorithmic time complexity: you will only have to click X amount of times to fill up your inventory. This is pretty much a constant. However, depending on the duration and difficulty of the Raid, you will be working a lot harder to make those rods! Ask someone like Cyricus whether he'd like VI to look at how often he has to make rods (maybe implement the mass rod summon AA people talk about) or a /drop command <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><center><img src="http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/hog.gif">

