I'm  not gonna get into how flawed autoequip still is, especially in intense video lag situations. Let's just say, the less we have to reach for the mouse, the less obnoxious playing the mage class is, IMO.<br>
<br>
Nothing I hate more than applications which force me to use the mouse... that little pos, sure the mouse is a cute idea, but totally flawed and worthless.<br>
<br>
I avoid auto equip trick at all costs. I refuse to move the mouse to a very small area of the screen and click. I will use 3rd person view alt+pgup unless there's a mob with a huge hit box blocking my drops that way. I'd rather press 6 buttons then reach for the mouse than reach for the mouse, 1 foot to the right, grab the mouse, find where it is on the screen, maneuver it to the right place, and click. Not to mention not being able to mem spells or loot crap without another 10 extra mouse movements and clicks, especially in EQ where graphix lag also lags the mouse.<br>
<br>
Krilen, anti-mouse nazi<br>
